Aircraft disinsection requirements not yet archived
[1
Date: Fri, 22 Oct 1999 08:55:45 -0500
From: Kathleen Harrington <kharrington@mail.vetmed.lsu.edu>

The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, in the Travel Information
section of their website, have a document entitled, "Spraying Aircraft for
Insects - Disinsection," that briefly explains the process and lists areas
in which travelers may expect to encounter it. See
<http://www.cdc.gov/travel/sprayair.htm>
